execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/adversarial-check-between-phases.md:10:Run a **lightweight adversarial check after Phase 2** (numerical/construction phase) and **before committing to Phase 3** (extended computation phase). Early reframing is far more valuable than corrections after the long computation is done. Specifically: after the first quantitative findings are in, have an explorer ask "which of these findings are genuinely novel vs. known?" and "which are artifacts of the approximation vs. fundamental physics?" before designing the next expensive explorations.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/adversarial-check-between-phases.md:24:For the between-phases adversarial check, a focused prompt works better than a full adversarial review:
execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/instruct-incremental-writing.md:41:- **yang-mills strategy-002 exploration-001** — Explorer composed a ~500-line report in one large Write call. This took approximately 17 minutes (62-second high-effort thinking phase followed by a single massive write). The goal did not include an incremental writing instruction. Adding "write each section as you complete it" to the goal would have distributed the write time across the exploration and prevented this terminal stall pattern.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/decomposition-audit-before-attacking-barrier.md:24:Before any phase that attempts to improve, circumvent, or close a known mathematical barrier. Specifically:
execution/agents/library/factual/classicality-budget/INDEX.md:3:The classicality budget: a universal, model-independent upper bound on quantum Darwinism redundancy derived from Bekenstein/holographic entropy bounds. R_delta <= (S_max / S_T) - 1 constrains how many independent observers can verify the same classical fact within a bounded region. The multi-fact extension M * (1 + R) <= S_max/S_T gives the fundamental trade-off between richness and objectivity. Novelty verdict: PARTIALLY KNOWN (Novel Synthesis) — structural form exists (Tank 2025), physical Bekenstein grounding is novel. Adversarial stress-test: 2 SERIOUS objections survived (catch-22 and triviality), none FATAL; **structural catch-22 PARTIALLY RESOLVED by holographic reformulation (E007)**. Operational budget (thermodynamic entropy) confirms non-constraining for all non-BH systems; BH Hawking radiation gives R_δ ≈ −0.997 universally for any BH mass. **Experimental regime survey (E003): three systems in TIGHT regime (R_max < 10): BEC at L=1μm, 20-ion trap at n̄=0.01, 10nm GaAs dot at 4K; ion trap phase transition at n̄_c ≈ 0.003. Island formula/Page curve (E004): two-stage classicality structure confirmed quantitatively; "interior classicality at Page time" = restatement of HQEC. 14 findings.**
execution/agents/library/factual/classicality-budget/INDEX.md:19:- **ion-trap-classicality-transition-protocol.md** -- Predicted classicality phase transition in 20-ion trap at n̄_c ≈ 0.003: below this occupation number, classicality budget FORBIDS any redundant classical copies. Detailed 6-step experimental protocol (n̄ sweep, quantum state tomography, shadow tomography). Feasible with current technology for N=10-20, n̄=0.01-0.1.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:2:topic: Definition-extraction explorations gate computation phases
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:10:Before committing to a computation phase, run a definition-extraction exploration ("Phase 0") that reads the primary source and extracts the exact mathematical definition of the quantity, event, or theorem object to be measured or proved. This prevents the most wasteful failure mode: computing the wrong thing because the team's mental model of the target object was incorrect.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:16:- **exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit exploration-001** — The local library already had the mechanism map and the candidate exact-NS objections. What it lacked was the exact amplitude-level interaction language. Pulling one precise helical-triad law from primary sources was enough to close the definition gap and produce a testable exact-support object. The computation phase was blocked on the missing exact law, not on a full literature survey.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:17:- **exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall exploration-001** — The helical singleton and packet definitions were already exhausted. The successful Phase 0 move was different: exact coarse-grained forward flux `Pi_ell` plus a local subscale witness `W_{ell,rho,r}` gave a faithful physical-space event directly on exact Navier-Stokes. The missing layer was an observability-convention ledger, not a new reduced dynamical model.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:21:1. Before any computation-heavy phase, allocate one exploration to read the primary source(s) and extract exact definitions.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:24:4. If the extracted definition differs from the team's working assumption, redesign the computation phase before proceeding.
execution/agents/library/meta/methodology/definition-extraction-gates-computation.md:26:6. If the local library already fixes the architecture and objections, ask whether a single exact law or definition from the primary source is the only missing ingredient. Often that one missing exact-language layer is enough to unlock the whole next phase.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:3:Statistical properties of non-trivial Riemann zeta zeros and their connection to random matrix theory (GUE). Computational verification of the Montgomery-Odlyzko law, Berry's spectral saturation prediction (confirmed qualitatively and quantitatively), constraints on the hypothetical Riemann operator, trace formula limitations, empirical tests of arithmetic matrix constructions (real symmetric and complex-phase), **Li's criterion computational verification**, and **computation method reliability**. **Berry's diagonal approximation confirmed: prime sums reproduce K(τ) ramp with MAD=14.5%. All Dirichlet character constructions proved structurally GOE (algebraic proof + numerical confirmation). Adversarial review (E007): pair correlation MRD ≤10% is generic to all GUE-class matrices; Von Mangoldt amplitude unnecessary; test cannot discriminate GOE from GUE at N=500. Final novelty verdicts (E008): N²/p scaling and Dirichlet impossibility SUPPORTED; C1 rigidity WEAK; Berry saturation NOT NOVEL; prime form factor normalization WEAK. Flat-amplitude test (E009): Von Mangoldt amplitude does NOT cause Δ₃ anomaly; C1 rigidity claim RETRACTED (NOT NOVEL); finite-size N=500 GUE Δ₃_sat = 0.23–0.26 (NOT the infinite-N theory ~0.566); 40% gap to zeta zeros (0.155) confirmed and unresolved.** **Li's criterion (S003-E002): all 500 λ_n positive (n=1..500, 2000 zeros, 50-digit precision); convergence by phase cancellation (|1−1/ρ|=1 exactly); truncation ratio r≈0.646 uniform; Coffey asymptotic 2.44× better than BL; GUE correlation 97.1% but zeta λ_n < GUE λ_n for n>300 (super-rigidity); no prime/FFT structure in residuals.** **R₂→Δ₃ integral chain UNRELIABLE at N=2000 (S003-E003): 43% overestimate; K→Σ₂→Δ₃ also fails (~2× normalization); direct sliding-window method is reliable.** **N²/p universal scaling REJECTED (S003-E004): peak N²/p varies 200–309 across N=250, 500, 1000; peak β_max decreases with N (1.32→1.15→1.02); N=500 observation still SUPPORTED but "universal" claim rejected; Brody MLE partially consistent for N≥500.** **Gauss Δ₃ rigidity hierarchy (S003-E005): Gauss matrices Δ₃_sat = 0.415–0.559 (all less rigid than N=500 random-phase ensembles at 0.23–0.29); complete hierarchy zeta(0.155) < C1/GUE_N500(0.23–0.29) < Gauss(0.42–0.56) < GUE∞(0.58); β and Δ₃ decouple; random phases more rigid than arithmetic phases.** **Super-rigidity mechanism (S003-E006): Berry's direct formula works (0.154 at T=600, 1% error), K→Σ₂→Δ₃ integral fails; K_primes(cap) only 3.3% above GUE through integral — tau<1 differences negligible; super-rigidity arises from saturation mechanism (log-log growth), not K(τ<1) fine structure.** (**Updated S003-E007**: Li-GUE crossover novelty CONFIRMED 4/5 by literature search — zero prior papers compare λ_n^zeta to λ_n^GUE; Berry formula growing error assessed as sparse-sampling artifact.) (**Updated S003-E008**: truncation validation at 5000 zeros; GUE λ_n scales linearly with N.) (**Updated S003-E009**: Li-GUE crossover **RESOLVED: TRUNCATION ARTIFACT** — matched K=N test at 500/1000/2000/3000/5000 shows ratio crosses 1.0 between K=2000-3000, reaching 1.090 at K=5000; root cause: linear scaling density mismatch; comparison methodology remains novel (4/5), specific crossover claim RETRACTED; correct comparison requires unfolding to unit mean spacing.) 24 findings.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:29:- **arithmetic-matrix-operators-poisson-failure.md** — Von Mangoldt Toeplitz, Möbius Toeplitz, and Hankel matrices (all real symmetric) fail to produce GUE statistics: all Toeplitz variants → Poisson (β=−0.31 to −0.36); Hankel → intermediate Poisson-GOE (β=0.44). Matrix structure determines universality class more than arithmetic content. Real symmetric matrices are capped at GOE (β≤1). Updated: complex-phase prediction confirmed — see complex-phase-matrices-gue-approach.md.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:30:- **complex-phase-matrices-gue-approach.md** — Complex Hermitian matrices with random phases are GUE-class by KS criterion (KS_GUE=0.028–0.042); β estimate 1.18–1.67 depending on realization (high variability). Gauss sum phases are permanently GOE (β≤1.2 for all p; β→2 hypothesis REFUTED by prime sweep). Key principle: phase φ(j,k) must depend jointly on both indices. Odd Dirichlet characters fail (zero matrix). Toeplitz zeta phases fail (Poisson). **All Dirichlet character constructions (including even characters χ₅, χ₁₃) proved structurally GOE by algebraic proof (E006): multiplicative route → Hermitianized becomes real symmetric via Re(χ(j)χ(k))=cos(g_j+g_k); factorizable route → unitarily equivalent to real. No Hermitian Dirichlet construction can achieve GUE. β→2 via Dirichlet hypothesis REFUTED.** *Updated: S002-E005 Gauss sweep refutation; S002-E006 Dirichlet algebraic proof.*
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:31:- **c1-constraint-scorecard.md** — 10-constraint RMT evaluation of C1 (random-phase construction): **Corrected (S002-E005): 3 PASS** (pair correlation MRD=7.9%, KS_GUE=0.042, form factor), **4 PARTIAL** (β=1.18, Δ₃_sat=0.285≈50% of GUE, Σ²(L)), **2 NOT COMPUTED** (plateau, higher-order), **1 N/A**. **Adversarial review (S002-E007): pair correlation PASS is a 5-realization averaging artifact (individual mean 15.5%, 0/20 pass); Von Mangoldt amplitude unnecessary (pure GUE achieves 7.8%); restated claim status SUPPORTED not ESTABLISHED.** Anomalous rigidity: C1 is twice more rigid than GUE but less rigid than actual zeta zeros (0.156).
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:32:- **gauss-sum-phases-permanently-goe.md** — Gauss sum phases H_{jk} ∝ exp(2πi·jk/p) are permanently GOE-class (β≤1.2 for all p); hypothesis β→2 as p→∞ REFUTED. Maximum β=1.154 at p=809. β is non-monotone and DECREASES for large p (β=0.086 at p=99991). Optimal N²/p ≈ 250–310 for N=500; physical interpretation: chirp phase cycle count. GUE is structurally inaccessible from Gauss sum construction. *Updated S003-E004: universality caveat resolved — NOT universal.*
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:37:- **gauss-delta3-rigidity-hierarchy.md** — Gauss Δ₃ spectral rigidity computed for 6 primes (p=97 to 9973): Δ₃_sat ranges 0.415–0.559 — ALL less rigid than N=500 random-phase constructions (0.23–0.29). Complete rigidity hierarchy: zeta(0.155) < N=500 GUE/C1(0.23–0.29) < Gauss-best/p=809(0.415) < Gauss-worst/p=9973(0.559) ≈ GUE∞(0.581). β and Δ₃ decouple: random phases produce stronger long-range correlations than arithmetic Gauss phases despite similar β. Pair correlation MRD for Gauss (15–18%) universally worse than C1 (7.9%). *From S003-E005.*
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/INDEX.md:52:- **li-phase-cancellation-structure.md** — |1 − 1/ρ| = 1 exactly for zeros on the critical line (VERIFIED by computation). The Li series converges by phase cancellation, not amplitude decay. λ_n = Σ 2(1 − cos(n·θ_k)). Li's criterion equivalent to a Fourier-transform constraint on zero phase distribution. Off-line zeros would break pure phase structure. Algebraically trivial but interpretively useful framing.
