execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:7:- **tao-averaged-ns-delayed-transfer-circuit.md** — Tao's averaged-NS blowup mechanism is a deliberately engineered five-mode delayed-abrupt-transfer circuit embedded in a shell cascade, not a vague "dyadic cascade" slogan. Averaging preserves energy cancellation/scaling but not the exact local NS tensor structure. Key reduced roles: `X1,n` carrier, `X2,n` clock, `X3,n` tiny trigger, `X4,n` conduit, `X1,n+1` next carrier. The sharpened exact-NS firewall question is whether real triads can realize the same independently tuned couplings/signs while suppressing parasitic interactions; later precursor work fixes the best physical-space handoff as forward flux plus subscale witness gain. [VERIFIED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:8:- **exact-helical-near-closed-tao-circuit-definition.md** — Phase 0 definition gate PASSES: a near-closed Tao circuit can be stated exactly on a finite sign-closed helical support with a five-role target hypergraph and a coefficient-weighted leakage ratio. Exact data and user tolerances are now explicitly separated. Singleton amplitude-level bookkeeping is the preferred Phase 1 object; packet-energy models are backup only. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:9:- **exact-trigger-object-not-standalone.md** — A Tao-style tiny trigger is not a standalone theorem object in exact NS. Making "tiny before threshold, decisive after threshold" precise forces the full carrier/clock/conduit/output chain back in, so the faithful trigger object is just the prior five-role helical model with `a3` distinguished. The predecessor singleton negative and packet non-canonicity therefore transfer immediately. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:10:- **exact-singleton-tao-circuit-nonembeddability.md** — The preferred singleton-support exact Tao-circuit object is structurally impossible. The desired `a1^2 -> a2` and `a1^2 -> a3` channels force roles 2 and 3 onto the same conjugate wavevector pair, after which the amplifier `a2 a3 -> a3` cannot satisfy exact triad closure for any sign choice. Stronger than a leakage obstruction: the sharp exact object dies before coefficient analysis. [COMPUTED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:12:- **exact-ns-helical-sign-canonicity-failure.md** — Splitting the packet sign defect into `SD_part` and `SD_target` sharpens the obstruction language but does not canonize the packet object. `SD_part` fails conjugate-pair representative invariance and moves under packet refinement, while `SD_target` and `Leak` still depend on non-canonical desired-triad bookkeeping, so Phase 1 still stops at canonicity failure. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:13:- **exact-ns-physical-space-delayed-transfer-event.md** — The faithful physical-space exact-NS analogue of Tao's delayed handoff is a localized burst of positive forward interscale flux across one coarse-graining scale together with abrupt gain in a subscale band-energy witness after an earlier quiet interval. Filtering is observability, not reduced dynamics; Duchon-Robert is backup only; the clean no-hidden-transfer continuation on the selected same-family precursor is later closed negatively. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:14:- **exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-pair.md** — The preferred earlier-warning pair for the exact delayed-transfer event is cumulative positive `Pi_ell` mass on the disjoint predecessor slab of the same parabolic cylinder. It survives the tautology screen because it drops the later witness clause and stays on a fixed earlier interval; Duchon-Robert is backup only; later work shows the pair still lacks the exact backward-memory needed for an identity-only no-hidden-transfer theorem. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:15:- **exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-no-backward-memory.md** — The preferred delayed-transfer precursor pair fails structurally at the theorem stage: subtracting the filtered balances at `ell/rho` and `ell` controls only the final-window witness gain, boundary transport, and viscous band terms, while the earlier slab `R_-` never appears. So no theorem `P_flux^-(R_-) <= epsilon => E_flux impossible` follows from exact identities alone. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:16:- **exact-ns-triadic-coefficient-rigidity.md** — Exact NS gives one Fourier-triad interaction law with geometry- and projector-fixed coefficients, not Tao's five independently engineered gate strengths. The live question is whether any exact support can realize Tao's full sign/size hierarchy inside that rigidity. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:17:- **exact-ns-unavoidable-spectator-couplings.md** — Exact NS activates the full projected triad network plus mirror-mode bookkeeping, so Tao's desired channels do not come alone. After the definition gate, the stress test is exact: write the desired / internal-leakage / external-leakage ledger on a minimal helical support and see whether any adversarially favorable helicity choice can keep leakage genuinely subordinate. [CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:25:- **spectral-ladyzhenskaya-negative-result.md** — Spectral support alone CANNOT improve sharp Ladyzhenskaya constant as worst-case bound. LP cross terms dominate (63% for Kolmogorov). Phase-optimized fields achieve near-sharp constants. **E008: phase optimization may be stuck in local optima (L-BFGS-B on non-convex landscape); Bernstein inequality offers alternative interpolation path.** Verdict: INCONCLUSIVE (directionally correct, not rigorous). [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/INDEX.md:26:- **gaussian-effective-ladyzhenskaya.md** — In the Gaussian random-phase regime (CLT), C_{L,eff} = 3^{1/4}(||f||/||∇f||)^{3/4}. For Kolmogorov spectra: C_{L,eff} ≈ 1.707 × Re^{-3/8}. TYPICAL-case only, not a bound. [COMPUTED, CHECKED]
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/arithmetic-matrix-operators-poisson-failure.md:69:The von Mangoldt Hankel matrix with **complex-valued entries** — e.g., H_{ij} = Λ(i+j)·e^{iθ(i+j)} for some phase function θ — could potentially break time-reversal symmetry and push from β=0.44 (partial GOE) toward β=2 (GUE). This is the natural extension: the Hankel structure already introduces partial repulsion; adding complex phases removes the real-symmetric constraint that caps β at 1.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/arithmetic-matrix-operators-poisson-failure.md:71:**Update (2026-03-27, strategy-002 exploration-001):** This prediction was confirmed. Complex Hermitian matrices with random phases achieve β=1.675 (approaching GUE); Gauss sum phases achieve β=1.092 (GOE). The key constraint: phases must depend jointly on (j,k), not just |j-k|. See `complex-phase-matrices-gue-approach.md` for full results and `c1-constraint-scorecard.md` for the 10-constraint evaluation.
execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/one-task-per-exploration.md:50:- **riemann-hypothesis s002-meta-exploration-005** — Exploration-005 had Part A (recompute pair correlation and Δ₃ for the C1 matrix using corrected formulas) and Part B (sweep Gauss sum phases across multiple primes). Both used the same matrix construction; neither depended on the other's result. The exploration delivered both results cleanly. Contrast: combining "build new theory + attack it" would be a cognitive multi-task and should be split.
execution/agents/library/factual/stochastic-electrodynamics/sed-3d-zpf-correlator.md:135:In 1D, all modes share the same propagation direction → perfectly constructive interference at resonance. In 3D, off-axis k-vectors contribute phase factors e^{i(ω/c)d cos θ}, which partially cancel under spherical integration. This introduces destructive interference that reduces amplitude by ~1/d for large d.
execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/gaussian-effective-ladyzhenskaya.md:10:For fields with many random-phase Fourier modes, the Central Limit Theorem gives a Gaussian pointwise distribution. In this regime, the effective Ladyzhenskaya constant has an explicit formula depending only on the energy spectrum, with a clean Re^{-3/8} scaling for Kolmogorov turbulence.
