execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/gaussian-effective-ladyzhenskaya.md:53:The GOAL.md reports measured C_eff ≈ 0.147 at Re~1000, vs. Gaussian prediction of 0.125. The phases add ~18% to concentration above Gaussian (intermittency). This confirms the Gaussian formula is a reasonable estimate for typical NS flows but NOT a bound. [COMPUTED]
