execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/gauss-sum-phases-permanently-goe.md:10:Complex Hermitian matrices with Gauss sum phases H_{jk} = Λ(|j-k|+1) × exp(2πi·jk/p) (1-indexed, prime p) are **permanently GOE-class**. The hypothesis that β → 2 (GUE) as p → ∞ is **definitively refuted** by direct computation across primes from p=97 to p=99991.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/gauss-sum-phases-permanently-goe.md:30:1. **p < 500 (N²/p > 500):** β ≈ 0.5–0.9 (moderate GOE; phases repeat many times → structured)
