execution/agents/library/factual/barandes-stochastic/INDEX.md:3:Physical content assessment of Barandes' indivisible stochastic processes (ISP) framework for quantum mechanics. **Level 2+ reformulation** (refined from Level 2 after E005 adversarial review): genuine conceptual/foundational value (complex numbers derivation, Tsirelson bound characterization, phase-freedom/realm-selection connection, measurement problem dissolution) but NO predictive or computational value. Feb 2026 paper cluster assessed (7 papers, CHSH/Tsirelson strongest). Tsirelson claim circularity **CONFIRMED** (E005: proof assumes unistochastic = Born rule QM; authors acknowledge). Amplituhedron comparison: Barandes significantly weaker (conceptual vs. operational value). **6 findings.** (UPDATED: barandes-stochastic E005 adversarial steelman.)
execution/agents/library/factual/barandes-stochastic/INDEX.md:11:- **fundamental-gaps-phase-erasure.md** -- Four fundamental limitations from phase erasure: (1) entanglement completely obscured -- same Gamma for singlet and maximally mixed, (2) no continuous generators -- no analog of Hermitian H, (3) QFT/Standard Model out of reach -- finite N, no particle creation, no Lorentz symmetry, (4) superposition invisible -- encoded only as non-factorizability.
