execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:3:Lessons about how to write exploration goals: scoping, specificity, context loading, output format, failure paths, and structural requirements. **45 entries.** (NEW: **require-harmless-change-invariance-for-observables** [exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck meta-001 — before Phase 1 computations, require new observables to survive conjugate-pair relabeling and harmless packet refinements]. UPDATED: **check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing** [exact-ns-helical-sign-bottleneck meta-001 — adding new observables to the same non-canonical object family does not reopen Phase 1]. Prior: **fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search** [exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-003 — after freezing the selected pair, first ask whether the exact identity has any backward-memory term linking the earlier slab to the later event; if not, stop rather than renaming the same defect]. Prior: **fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search** [exact-ns-hidden-precursor-firewall meta-002 — if Phase 0 already fixed the event cylinder, use the literal earlier slab as the precursor region and freeze the selected pair for the next theorem-target exploration]. Prior: **check-faithful-support-shrinkage-before-narrowing** [exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall meta-001 — before launching a narrowed mechanism mission, test whether the narrowed feature actually reduces the faithful exact support; if not, predecessor negatives may already transfer]. UPDATED: **require-mechanism-layer-maps** [exact-ns-tiny-trigger-firewall meta-001 — causal roles like trigger/clock/conduit are not standalone theorem objects; name the surrounding chain that makes them meaningful]. Prior: **build-adversarial-suppression-into-first-audit** [exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit meta-001 — when testing a leakage/impossibility claim, include at least one configuration chosen to suppress the alleged obstruction]. UPDATED: **require-mechanism-layer-maps** [exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit meta-001 — if the reduced mechanism is quadratic, represent it as a monomial hypergraph rather than just a node graph]. Prior: anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-002 updates, anatomy-of-averaged-ns-blowup-firewall meta-001, allow-analytic-extremizer-over-computation [vasseur-pressure S2-E008], adversarial-review-needs-complete-parallel-context [S2-E007], adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure update [S2-E007], require-sensitivity-table-for-proof-analysis [S2-E001], one-task-per-exploration [E007], ask-what-replaces-the-bottleneck [E008], flag-cross-framework-connections [E006].)
execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:46:- **adversarial-proof-review-structure.md** — **[NEW barandes-stochastic E005, UPDATED yang-mills-conjecture E007, UPDATED navier-stokes E008]** For adversarial reviews of a specific proof, use a 4+1-step structure: (1) trace proof step by step, (2) identify key assumption, (3) check if derived or imported, (4) check prior art, **(5) check whether the proved statement actually implies the claimed conclusion**. Variants: always require steelman when adversarial likely negative; ask "does the paper acknowledge its own limitations?"; **for matrix inequality proofs, verify reduction from operator bound to quadratic form bound**; **pre-specify 3-4 attack vectors per claim** [NS E008 — directed reviewer to productive criticisms, caught apples-to-oranges comparison and (5/9)^{1/4} misattribution]; **dual-mode adversarial: standard explorer (logic+literature) + math explorer (recomputation)** [NS E008 — standard-only missed opportunity for independent numerical verification]. Distinct from adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure (multi-claim review) and adversarial-check-between-phases (timing).
execution/agents/library/meta/goal-design/INDEX.md:48:- **adversarial-review-needs-complete-parallel-context.md** — **[NEW, vasseur-pressure S2-E007]** When launching an adversarial review in parallel with constructive explorations, the reviewer may lack findings from parallel work. Either launch adversarial reviews AFTER constructive explorations complete (preferred), or include summaries of parallel work as supplementary context. S2-E007 flagged "non-CZ pressure incomplete" when S2-E006 had already resolved it. Distinct from adversarial-check-between-phases (timing), preload-context (general loading), adversarial-synthesis-goal-structure (output format).
execution/agents/library/factual/loop-quantum-gravity/predictions.md:17:The primary cosmological prediction: the Big Bang singularity is replaced by a Big Bounce. Quantum geometry creates a repulsive force that is negligible at low curvature but rises rapidly in the Planck regime, overwhelming classical gravitational attraction. A contracting phase precedes the current expanding phase. This result has been confirmed by rigorous numerical simulations and shown to be robust across multiple models.
execution/agents/library/factual/loop-quantum-gravity/predictions.md:31:Quantum geometric effects seed asymmetric perturbations during the bounce phase of collapsing matter, producing gravitational wave bursts with mass-dependent frequencies (arXiv:2511.05624).
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:38:1. **Tournament → Deep Dive → Mandatory Adversarial is an effective three-phase arc for constructive research.** The scoring metric (constraint catalog) makes the tournament objective and the Phase 2 allocation evidence-based. Phase 3 must be mandatory with minimum allocation (not optional).
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:40:2. **Adversarial review is the highest-ROI phase.** Strategy-001 skipped it and reported claims that wouldn't survive. Strategy-002 ran it and caught two false claims. The adversarial review (E007) was the single most valuable exploration in the entire strategy. **Make adversarial the FIRST thing in Phase 3, not the last.**
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-riemann-hypothesis-learnings.md:46:5. **Prescribe the specific control experiments in the strategy.** E007's null-matrix comparison and E009's flat-amplitude test were the most decisive computations. Both were designed by the strategizer, not prescribed. Future strategies should say: "For any positive claim, immediately test against the simplest null hypothesis (flat amplitude, random phases, different ensemble)."
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/szz-lemma-4-1-hessian-slack.md:10:Numerical measurement of the SZZ Lemma 4.1 Hessian bound shows it is **12-170× loose** across all β values and dimensions tested (3D and 4D). The bound |HessS(v,v)| ≤ 8(d-1)Nβ|v|² is never approached on typical Gibbs configurations, and adversarial search (gradient ascent, aligned configs, eigenvalue search) also fails to saturate it. The mechanism is plaquette cancellation: the bound assumes worst-case alignment, but actual plaquettes contribute with random phases and destructively interfere.
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/szz-lemma-4-1-hessian-slack.md:88:3. But contributions have **random phases** → destructive interference
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/szz-lemma-4-1-hessian-slack.md:129:1. **Replace linear by √-scaling:** Bound H_norm ≈ c·√(# plaquettes) instead of linear in plaquettes. Account for random phase cancellations.
execution/agents/library/factual/riemann-hypothesis/li-gue-comparison-super-rigidity.md:49:Super-rigid spacing (as in zeta) → more evenly distributed phases theta_k → more efficient cancellation in Sum cos(n*theta_k) → smaller lambda_n at large n. The GUE model captures 97% of Li coefficient structure but misses a correction that grows with n, reflecting arithmetic structure beyond random matrix universality.
