execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/INDEX.md:7:- **balaban-uv-stability.md** — Balaban's 14-paper RG program (1983-1989): proves UV stability of 4D lattice pure Yang-Mills in finite volume via four-phase construction (foundational tools → 3D proof → small-field 4D RG → large-field analysis). Precise theorem: partition function bounded uniformly as lattice spacing → 0. Also completes 3D UV stability (superrenormalizable case).
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/INDEX.md:29:- **szz-lemma-4-1-hessian-slack.md** — SZZ Lemma 4.1 Hessian bound |HessS(v,v)| ≤ 8(d-1)Nβ|v|² is **12-170× loose** across 3D and 4D lattices and all tested β values. **MAJOR FINDING.** 3D slack: 12-45× (β=0.02–2.0). 4D slack: 29-138× (β=0.02–1.0). Adversarial search (gradient ascent, aligned configs, eigenvalue search) gives ≥176× slack. **Counter-intuitive: 4D is tighter than 3D (more plaquettes → more cancellation).** Mechanism: plaquette contributions destructively interfere (random phases), but bound assumes worst-case alignment. Implied: if sharper analytic bound proven, SZZ threshold could reach β < 0.25 (12× improvement). CNS vertex bound also 90× above actual edge Hessian at β=0.02.
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/INDEX.md:37:- **other-modern-approaches.md** — Alternative UV stability proofs and continuum approaches: Faria da Veiga-O'Carroll (2019, simpler lattice proof), Magnen-Rivasseau-Sénéor (1993, continuum with IR cutoff), Charalambous-Gross YM heat flow regularization, Federbush phase cell approach.
execution/agents/library/factual/yang-mills/INDEX.md:39:- **finite-subgroup-convergence.md** — Monte Carlo evidence that binary icosahedral group (2I, order 120) reproduces SU(2) lattice Yang-Mills to < 0.5% for the plaquette and < 0.3% for the Creutz ratio (string tension proxy) across β = 1.0–4.0. All finite subgroups exhibit first-order bulk phase transitions at β_c ~ |G|^{0.6} → ∞; below the transition, confinement and area law are indistinguishable from SU(2). **[CONJECTURED]**: the barrier to extending Adhikari-Cao to SU(2) is technical (controlling |G|-dependence in bounds), not fundamental (the physics converges). Observable convergence rate ~ |G|^{-0.7 to -2.5}.
execution/agents/library/factual/quadratic-gravity-fakeon/experimental-signatures-beyond-cmb.md:40:QG+F-specific GW background from: (1) scalaron oscillation during reheating → f ~ 10⁸-10¹⁰ Hz; (2) possible ghost confinement transition at T ~ M_Planck → f ~ 10¹⁰ Hz; (3) CDT B-C phase transition → f ~ 10¹⁰ Hz. All at frequencies far above LISA (10⁻⁴-10⁻¹ Hz), LIGO (10-10³ Hz), and PTA (10⁻⁹-10⁻⁷ Hz). **NOT DETECTABLE.**
