execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-thermal-time-learnings.md:32:2. **The strategy should have made the adversarial review non-deferrable.** It was listed as "Phase 2, exploration 5: MANDATORY adversarial review" — but "mandatory" within a phase that the strategizer chose to skip. **Lesson: if adversarial review is truly mandatory, it should be Phase 1 (not Phase 2) or structurally enforced (e.g., "strategy is not complete until the adversarial exploration runs").**
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-yang-mills-validation-learnings.md:12:Three-phase adversarial audit: (1) Independent rederivation + novelty assessment + convention verification in parallel, (2) Numerical extensions (large lattice, SU(3), dimensional analysis), (3) Adversarial synthesis. 8 explorations, all mandatory, adversarial posture throughout. "Try to find errors, not confirm claims."
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-yang-mills-validation-learnings.md:46:5. **Numerical extensions as Phase 2 work well because they're independent of the proof audit.** Even when the proof has a gap, the numerics remain valid evidence. The phases should be truly parallel in this sense.
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-sed-learnings.md:12:A breadth-first frontier mapping: 3 parallel probes of independent systems (tunneling, coupled oscillators, hydrogen), followed by root cause diagnosis, then adversarial synthesis. Cross-phase rules: ALD mandatory (learned from Strategy-001), computation mandatory, pre-load verified formulas. Target: "minimal modification" question.
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-sed-learnings.md:22:1. **Double-check physical constants in the strategy itself.** The τ value for hydrogen was wrong by 60× in the exploration goal. The missionary should have verified τ = e²/(6πε₀mₑc³) in atomic units and written it explicitly in STRATEGY.md. Cross-phase rules should include "verify all physical constants against known references before any simulation."
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-sed-learnings.md:32:- **The tunneling formula R²=0.9998 was far stronger than expected.** I designed the probes as quick surveys, not expecting any of them to produce a publishable quantitative law. The formula emerged from E001 as a conjecture and was confirmed in E005 — the two-phase discovery→verification cycle worked perfectly.
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-002-sed-learnings.md:46:4. **Physical constant verification should be a cross-phase rule.** When simulations use physical units, wrong constants invalidate results even if the code is correct.
execution/agents/library/factual/causal-set-theory/de-sitter-cosmology.md:10:Ahmed and Rideout (2009) demonstrated that a large class of classical sequential growth (CSG) dynamical laws for causal sets naturally produce a cyclic universe with "expansion and contraction phases separated by origin elements." Immediately following each origin element -- a special singular point marking the boundary between cycles -- the effective dynamics yields "an initial period of de Sitter like exponential expansion."
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-vasseur-pressure-learnings.md:17:The strategizer correctly deviated from the strategy to insert Phase 1b/1c (4 explorations following leads from Phase 1) before the adversarial review. This was good judgment — the adversarial review would have just flagged these as unexplored leads. **Future strategies should include a "Lead Pursuit" phase between measurement and adversarial review as a prescribed option:** "If Phase 1 surfaces promising leads, the Strategizer may run up to N additional explorations before Phase 2, provided each is a single-task, literature-or-computation goal."
execution/agents/library/meta/missionary/strategy-001-vasseur-pressure-learnings.md:29:10 of 20 budget used. Clean stopping was possible because each negative result clearly closed a direction. The methodology's cross-phase rules (multi-IC validation, convergence checks) meant each negative was trustworthy. **Invest in making negative results DEFINITIVE (multi-IC, convergence-checked, multi-angle) so that directions stay closed. Ambiguous negatives lead to revisitation and wasted budget.**
