## Entries

- **tao-averaged-ns-delayed-transfer-circuit.md** — Tao's averaged-NS blowup mechanism is a deliberately engineered five-mode delayed-abrupt-transfer circuit embedded in a shell cascade, not a vague "dyadic cascade" slogan. Averaging preserves energy cancellation/scaling but not the exact local NS tensor structure. Key reduced roles: `X1,n` carrier, `X2,n` clock, `X3,n` tiny trigger, `X4,n` conduit, `X1,n+1` next carrier. The sharpened exact-NS firewall question is whether real triads can realize the same independently tuned couplings/signs while suppressing parasitic interactions; later precursor work fixes the best physical-space handoff as forward flux plus subscale witness gain. [VERIFIED]
