## 2026-04-01 Processing: exploration-003-quantitative-test-for-e-flux-p-flux-minus-report.md + meta-exploration-003.md

### Findings extracted (factual — exploration-003-quantitative-test-for-e-flux-p-flux-minus-report.md):

This exploration attacked the strongest physical-space precursor pair found so far and returned a structural negative rather than a proof-search failure.

- The preferred delayed-transfer precursor pair `E_flux` / `P_flux^-` fails structurally: the exact filtered local energy balance over the later witness window contains no term involving the earlier slab `R_-`, so no identity-only theorem of the form `P_flux^-(R_-) <= epsilon => E_flux impossible` is available -> filed at `factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-no-backward-memory.md` (NEW)
- The pair-selection entry is now sharpened with the theorem-stage verdict: the pair remains the least-tautological candidate, but its clean no-hidden-transfer route is closed because the later witness identity never sees the earlier slab -> incorporated into `factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-delayed-transfer-precursor-pair.md` (UPDATE)
- The event-side definition is also sharpened: the physical-space event survives intact, but its strongest same-family precursor continuation is now negative unless extra temporal-memory input is added -> incorporated into `factual/navier-stokes/exact-ns-physical-space-delayed-transfer-event.md` (UPDATE)

### Findings extracted (meta — meta-exploration-003.md):

- After freezing the selected pair, the first theorem-facing audit should ask whether the exact identity has any backward-memory term linking the earlier slab to the later event; if not, stop early unless the goal explicitly names an extra hypothesis -> incorporated into `meta/goal-design/fix-observability-conventions-before-precursor-search.md` (UPDATE)
- Backup observables less directly tied to the witness channel should only be promoted if they repair the structural memory defect rather than merely renaming the same mechanism family -> incorporated into the same goal-design update (not separate)
- The launched math-explorer stall after context loading was SKIPPED as a duplicate operational lesson (covered by `meta/system-behavior/explorer-stalling-and-nudge-pattern.md`); the only mission-specific wrinkle was that manual recovery was cheap because the decisive audit was conceptual rather than computational

